### For some reason, requested naming worked in local `osc build` but not on OBS:
# python (>= 2.6.6-3~) | python2
### (maybe due to versioning?) Anyhow, data in this control file only double-checks
### that .dsc made a good buildroot so we can not-check the confusing lines here.

Package: malamute
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Build-Depends: libzmq3-dev, libczmq-dev
Multi-Arch: same
Description: All the enterprise messaging patterns in one box
 .
 Malamute is a messaging broker and a protocol for enterprise messaging.
 Malamute helps to connect the pieces in a distributed software system.
 It includes:
 * Live Streamed Data
 * On-Demand Streamed Data
 * Publish-and-Subscribe (Pub-Sub)
 * Direct Messaging
 * Service Requests
 * Credit Based Flow Control (CBFC)
 .
 This package provides the daemon itself.

